            "chips_text": "Pendant",
            "button_text": "View more design",
            "fact_heading": "Facts",
            "fact_text": "Ethical & Conflict FreeTraditional labour intensive diamond mining, while regulated in many regions now, has been historically linked to financing conflict in politically unstable areas, human rights violations, unsafe and forced labour conditions among other ethical issues. While initiatives such as Kimberley Process try to control the trade of conflict diamonds and trace their origins, the complex nature of global supply chains cannot guarantee total traceability of every natural stone. Being ethical, sustainable, and conflict free is one of the most well known advantages of owning a lab grown diamond. These lab created gems completely eliminate these concerns. These gems are formed in hitech controlled lab environments, offering complete traceability from start to finish. These diamonds are an ethical choice, from their origin to their purchase. There are no human rights violations, or risks of contributing to conflict zones, displacement of communities and natural habitats, or environmental concerns. If you’re someone who values ethical purchases, social responsibility and sustainability, lab grown diamonds are made just for you! As society continues to make sustainability and ethical purchases a priority in their buying decisions, lab grown diamonds continue to grow in popularity."
          }
        },
        "collection_block_TAhyWx": {
          "type": "collection_block",
          "settings": {
            "collection": "14kt-collection",
            "chips_text": "Earring",
            "button_text": "View more design",
            "fact_heading": "Facts",
            "fact_text": "Same Sparkle, Same BrillianceThere’s a common misconception that lab grown diamonds are not “real” diamonds. This is far from true. Not only are lab grown and mined natural diamonds physically and visually identical, they are also chemically the same. They’re made up of pure carbon molecules arranged in a crystal structure known as the cubic lattice. This is the structure that gives diamonds their hardness and durability, giving them a rating of 10 on the Mohs scale. While the two diamonds have different origins, they are chemically the same. Meaning, all other properties are the same as well, for example, these lab grown gems carry the same refractive index, durability, and brilliance as their natural counterparts.Lab grown diamonds undergo the same crystallization process as natural diamonds except under controlled conditions and shorter timelines. Due to lab grown diamonds being the same chemically as their mined counterparts, even trained gemologists can not differentiate between the two without specialised lab equipment. That’s not it! Lab grown and natural diamonds are not only graded and certified by the same bodies that grade and certify mined diamonds, such as GIA and IGI, they are also evaluated and priced on the same parameters as the mined diamonds, i.e., cut, color, clarity, and carat weight."
          }
